Create backend/src/agents/preview/agent-preview.service.ts — import { Agent } from '@mastra/core/agent'. Injectable service with method streamPreview(dto: AgentPreviewDto, userId: string, res: Response). Creates a throwaway Agent({name: 'preview', instructions: dto.instructions, model: dto.model || 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6'}). Calls agent.stream({messages: [{role: 'user', content: dto.message}]}). Iterates result.textStream (AsyncIterable) inside try/catch. For each chunk: res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify({text: chunk})}

`). After loop: res.write('data: {"done":true}

'). Finally: res.end(). Wrap entire streaming in try/finally to ensure res.end() is called even on error.
